title: Agents Of SHIELD Season 4 Episode 14: Self Control Photos and Sneak Preview
text:
Agents Of SHIELD Season 4 Episode 14: Self Control Photos and Sneak Preview Jay Jayson Back to Article Image of 
Last Tuesday's episode of Agents of SHIELD ended on quite the cliffhanger. Upon returning to home base after their latest mission, Agents Fitz and Simmons discover someone has tampered with the LMD detector, and once they getting it working again, they learn Coulson, Mack, Daisy, and Mace have been replaced with LMDs. Uh-Oh Spaghettios! 
To get a taste of what's to come in the next episode, which is titled “Self Control,” watch the sneak preview in the video above and check out preview images in our gallery below. 
S.H.I.E.L.D. IS OVERRUN BY LMDs, AND THERE IS NO ONE TO TRUST - Suspicion turns to paranoia when the team doesn’t know who can be trusted as more LMDs infiltrate S.H.I.E.L.D. 
The regular cast features Clark Gregg as Agent Phil Coulson, Ming-Na Wen as Agent Melinda May, Chloe Bennet as Daisy Johnson, Iain De Caestecker as Agent Leo Fitz, Elizabeth Henstridge as Agent Jemma Simmons, Henry Simmons as Agent Alphonso “Mack” MacKenzie, and John Hannah as Holden Radcliffe. 
The guest cast includes Natalia Cordova-Buckley as Elena “Yo-Yo” Rodriguez, Jason O’Mara as Director Jeffrey Mace, Mallory Jansen as Aida 2.0, Briana Venskus as Agent Piper, Maximilian Osinki as Agent Davis, Zach McGowan as The Superior, Ricardo Walker as Agent Prince, and Cantrell Harris as Agent Fisher. 
“Self Control” was written and directed by Jed Whedon. 
Marvel’s Agents of SHIELD airs Tuesdays at 10 p.m. ET on ABC.
